title> Re: Dragon/Plane Scheduling Restrictions</span><hr size=1> I have been authorized to present Veterans Legion's official response to this. <br>
<br>
VL, along with around 30 other guilds, agreed to the calendar restrictions that can be found <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showMessage?topicID=603.topic">here.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Having never seen the rules that are now posted on the calendar page, I have no idea where they came from, but I do know that VL never agreed to them, and have not seen any information that any other guilds have, either. Until there is another Council of Guilds meeting, and new rules are voted on, Veterans Legion will abide by the rules they agreed to over a year ago, which you can read in the thread linked above. <br>
<br>
Now, having looked over the rules, and our scheduled raids, we have found that we were indeed in violation by having 2 PoH raids on back-to-back Sundays. The rule of having only one weekend date found on the other set of rules is not found anywhere in the agreed-to rules, and in fact, it is stipulated that all 3 of your raids can be weekend dates, just that they can not be to the same plane on the same weekend day two weeks in a row. <br>
<br>
I apologize for our mistake, and it has been corrected. I have cancelled the Jan 6 raid. The reason I chose that one was simply to foster amity between guilds on the server. I would point out that we did in fact post that raid first, and I could just have easily cancelled the Jan 13 raid instead. In the future, please do NOT try to schedule raids over the top of Veterans Legion raids. If you check around on the server, you will find that we have a good reputation, and do not do things like that. We expect the same treatment in return. If there is another incident involving someone posting over the top of our raids, we will not honor it, and will not give up our raid. If anyone finds a discrepancy in Veterans Legion raid scheduling that is against the CoG rules, then please post on our board, or email me at cuchulaine_eq@hotmail.com. If there is indeed a violation then we will correct it with expediency. However, simply scheduling on top of us will not solve the problem and will not be honored. I think you will find that if you work with us, you will get a lot better results than trying to go around us.<br>
<br>
Veterans Legion believes that the calendar is fair to everyone, and will stand behind it, but will not be muscled out of our fair share of raids by technicalities. If the server does indeed go to FCFS, I believe VL is now at a stage where we could still get our fair share of raids under such a system, so from that stand point, whether the calendar stays are not, we can deal with either. We would prefer the calendar, but you should remember that there are some guilds that do not. The calendar will only work so long as the vast majority of guilds work together, including communicating when there is a conflict.<br>
<br>
If you find a violation them inform us, and we will correct it. Do NOT try to correct it for us.  <p><h6><a href="mailto:cuchulaine_eq@hotmail.com">Geneze Angelfyre</a><br>
