<br>
1)  I don't believe Stony and Kelestra tried to &quot;fix&quot; the Vets reservation.  It was an honest mistake on their part.<br>
<br>
2)  Thanks for the generous tones from the guild who said they welcome &quot;violations&quot; being brought to their attention.  I no longer do that after a couple of times of doing similar things (not necessarily with these guilds), and being trashed on guild boards (one case was even after their own officers warned the members not to trash me).<br>
<br>
3)  I did not single out any guilds.  I merely looked at what I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> thought</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> were the rules and them pointed out.  While my statement about any guild who wants to can break whatever rules they want seemed to imply these guilds, they were not intended to.  I apologize for that.<br>
<br>
4) A limit of four open raids per month????  Get real !  I'm sorry, but that is not the way things are these days.  The large guilds are uninterested in the planes these days.  I know enchanters, mages, warriors, etc who have to schedule open raids in order to get the drops for their epic pieces since their guild won't schedule planes raids.  If we truly had only 4 open raids per month, the calendar would be empty.<br>
<br>
My only question is to wonder if it is better to allow whatever &quot;violations&quot; occur, since some semi-followed guidelines are better than none.  Or, to rework the rules in light of the current situation.  Of course, this is easy for me to say, since I would not be involved in it.<br>
<br>
Pinyon Treedotter<br>
Guardians of Knowledge<br>
